---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About martins1981 — a publication for engineers running production">
  <div style="padding-top:80px;">
    <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem 4rem;">

      <!-- Header -->
      <div style="border-bottom:1px solid #2a2a2a;padding-bottom:2rem;margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <span class="category-badge" style="display:block;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">About</span>
        <h1 style="font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:clamp(2.5rem,6vw,5rem);color:#ffffff;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.02em;line-height:1;">
          ABOUT MARTINS1981
        </h1>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="article-content">
        <p>
          <strong>martins1981</strong> is a publication for SREs, DevOps engineers, and platform teams who take their work seriously. We write about the hard parts of running production systems at scale — not the glossy conference-talk version, but the 3am version.
        </p>

        <blockquote>
          "The goal isn't uptime. The goal is understanding your systems well enough that downtime, when it comes, is brief, contained, and educational."
        </blockquote>

        <h2>What We Write About</h2>

        <p>
          Our coverage spans four core areas: <strong>SRE</strong> (on-call culture, SLOs, error budgets, incident response), <strong>DevOps</strong> (CI/CD pipelines, deployment practices, automation), <strong>Platform Engineering</strong> (Kubernetes operators, internal developer platforms, abstractions), and <strong>Incidents & Postmortems</strong> (what went wrong, why, and how to make sure it doesn't happen the same way twice).
        </p>

        <h2>Who We Are</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>Valdeci Martins</strong> is a Senior SRE Engineer with over a decade of experience running production systems for high-traffic applications. He has been paged at 3am more times than he cares to count, and has learned something meaningful from each one. He writes to capture those lessons in a form that other engineers can use.
        </p>

        <h2>Why "martins1981"</h2>

        <p>
          The name is simple: Martins, born 1981. No abstraction, no brand. Just an engineer writing about engineering.
        </p>

        <h2>The Technical Stack</h2>

        <p>
          This site is built with <strong>Astro</strong>, using <strong>TailwindCSS</strong> for styling and Markdown/MDX for content. It's intentionally minimal — no JavaScript frameworks, no tracking, no ads. Just articles.
        </p>

        <h2>Get in Touch</h2>

        <p>
          The best way to reach us is via the newsletter. If you have a topic suggestion, a postmortem you'd like to share (blameless, of course), or a correction to something we've written, we'd love to hear from you.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
